Participants.text:
A total of 41 right-handed Chinese Han subjects (21 SIVD patients and 20 normal controls (NC) were enrolled in this study at the Department of Radiology in the First Affiliated Hospital of Soochow University from June 2020 to January 2022. This study was approved by the ethics committees of the First Affiliated Hospital of Soochow University, and written informed consent was obtained from each subject prior to participation. All subjects underwent a cognitive test and 3.0-T whole brain MRI scanning. Beijing version of Montreal cognitive assessment (MoCA) was utilized for general cognition assessment (Lu et al., 2011). Executive function was evaluated using the Color-Word Stroop Test, with reaction time in recognizing word color (Stroop test 1) and accuracy (Stroop test 2) serving as judgment criteria. Subsequently, Speed-Accuracy Trade-off (SAT) scores were calculated as accuracy ()reaction time (van Uden et al., 2015).
SIVD patients met the following criteria (Liu et al., 2014;Roman et al., 2002) The exclusion criteria were as follow: (1) metabolic conditions, such as hypothyroidism or folic acid deficiencies;
(2) a history of stroke; (3) central nervous system diseases that could cause cognitive decline, such as PD, epilepsy, MS. Subjects with contraindications for MR scanning were also excluded.
